The Credit Card Approval Prediction project successfully demonstrates the complete machine learning workflow, including data preprocessing, feature engineering, model training, evaluation, and deployment using Flask. Multiple classification algorithms were explored, and the Random Forest model was selected based on its performance.

A user-friendly web application was developed to allow users to enter applicant information and instantly predict whether a credit card application is likely to be approved or rejected. The application was successfully deployed and tested through a live demo.

This project provided practical experience in Python, Machine Learning, Flask web development, data preprocessing, model evaluation, and deployment. It also strengthened understanding of how machine learning can be applied to solve real-world problems in the banking and financial sector.
